ws.rocket.path

Class TreeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • ws.rocket.path.TreeNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class TreeNode
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A data structure which can be used for composing trees. A tree node can have a key, a value, and any amount of child tree nodes. Note that the types for key and value are not predefined nor mandatory. Also note that this class does not enforce any rules upon the key and value object (including uniqueness).

    Since a tree usually has many leaf nodes, which don't contain child-nodes, a special value instance is used for noting an empty array of child-nodes. It helps to consume less runtime memory and also makes null-checks against child-nodes array redundant. However, any one, who should synchronize over empty children array, may run into problems, since the array is shared over tree node instances.

    This tree node can be constructed only once. In addition, TreeNode is serializable as long as its keys, values and children are also serializable.

    See Also:
    KeyBuilder, Serialized Form
